Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced), separating whites from greens. Dice @tomato{1}(diced) into ½-inch pieces. Trim and quarter @mini cucumber{1}(trimmed and quartered) lengthwise; slice crosswise into ½-inch pieces. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}(zested and quartered). Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}(minced). Finely chop @dill{1/4%ounce}(finely chopped).

== Couscous ==

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2%tablespoon} in a small #pot{} over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}. Stir in @Israeli couscous{2.5%ounce}, @veggie stock concentrate{1}, @water{3/4%cup}, and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until tender, ~{6-8%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Cucumber-Tomato Salad ==

Meanwhile, in a small #bowl{}, combine tomato, cucumber, half the scallion greens, and half the @Greek vinaigrette{1.5%ounce}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Creamy Yogurt Sauce ==

In a second small bowl, combine @yogurt{4%tablespoon}, @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon}, juice from one lemon wedge, a large drizzle of olive oil, a pinch of garlic, and as much dill as you like. Add water 1 tsp at a time until sauce reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt and pepper.

== Shrimp ==

Rinse @shrimp{10%ounce} under cold water and pat dry with #paper towels{}.

Heat a large drizzle of olive oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add shrimp, @dried oregano{1%teaspoon}, remaining garlic, salt, and pepper. Cook, stirring, until opaque and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Remove pan from heat; stir in lemon zest and juice from remaining lemon wedges.

== Assembly ==

Stir remaining scallion greens and a drizzle of olive oil into pot with couscous; season with salt and pepper.

Divide couscous between bowls; top with shrimp and salad. Drizzle with sauce and serve.

> Shrimp are fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.